file=Product/loom/operational/skill/loom-skill-routing.md · l—s:loom — Skill Routing Map=Non-leader: law (the Evidence Gate — loom supplies experiment verdicts + PMF reads) + this routing decide WHICH skill WHEN.\n\n```\na plan rests on beliefs ─► assumption-mapping (surface, score, rank riskiest-first)\n│ top assumption\n▼\nexperiment-registry (QUERY: settled? stale? new?) ─settled─► cite verdict, don't re-run\n│ new/stale\n▼\nexperiment-discipline (cheapest falsifying test; decision rule + criteria FROZEN)\n│ (metric verifies instruments live first)\n▼\nverdict ─► experiment-registry (adopt/reject, append-only)\n"do we have PMF?" ─► pmf-scorecard (Ellis + retention flatness + qualitative, triangulated) ─► spec/marcus + registry\n```\n\nHandoffs out: spec (test-first verdicts in/out; experiment evidence) \· metric (experiment-instrumentation, retention curves) \· ux (qualitative why, assumption evidence) \· price (revenue experiments; viability) \· marcus/vista (PMF verdict → double-down/pivot; roadmap) \· proto/forge/scout (shared experiment + adopt-reject patterns) \· anneal (overturned verdicts → skill lessons).\nPrecedence: query the registry before running; criteria frozen before data; a near-miss is a miss; PMF thresholds are flagged rubric.\n